&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LEAD CARDIAC RADIOGRAPHER: Full time Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced radiographer to join our Cardiac Team in the Northampton Heart Centre in the role of a Band 7 Lead Cardiac Radiographer. We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated and dynamic individual who is willing to help develop our practice and move the service forward. You will have excellent organisational and communication skills. If you have extensive experience as a Cardiac Radiographer and a passion for team working then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be an enthusiastic, knowledgeable and motivated practitioner with excellent clinical and leadership skills and the ability to look after the day to-day running of a busy service and support the whole MDT with a variety of tasks. You will be expected to work closely with colleagues and members of the multidisciplinary team to develop new systems of work and foster collaborative working with a strong focus on patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cardiology and Radiology teams are friendly and highly skilled with a commitment to continuing professional development and all staff and are encouraged to be involved in training and audit and will be supported in the development of further skills as appropriate. As Lead Radiographer you may be required to assist in the daily management of the staff in other areas of Radiology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have extensive knowledge of IR(ME)R17 and IRR17 and will be expected to take on the role of RPS following appropriate training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants would be expected to be able to support the working hours of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Darryl North, Job title: Head of Imaging, Email address: Darryl.North@ngh.nhs.uk, Telephone number 01604 523570&lt;/p&gt;
